      <abstract>
        <p>Ruth Kramer Ziony letter on Steve Dougherty's December 31, 2006, article on winter travels in Russia</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding ''Holiday on Ice: With a Shot of Vodka on the Side'' by Steve Dougherty (Dec. 31): I am a 60-something female, and last December I traveled on my own to Moscow and St. Petersburg.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding ''Holiday on Ice: With a Shot of Vodka on the Side'' by Steve Dougherty (Dec. 31): I am a 60-something female, and last December I traveled on my own to Moscow and St. Petersburg.</p>
        <p>I'd like to mention more wonderful things about St. Petersburg. The Puppet Fairy Tale Theater puts on a magical series of plays for children based on classic nursery tales. Also, a trip to the post office yielded some of the most amazing souvenirs of my trip. There, I bought embossed stamps of the zodiac, which now hang over my computer.</p>
        <p>Ruth Kramer Ziony  Los Feliz, Calif.</p>
      </block>
